d inhibited the memoirist. Freed from convention, these writers, while close to death, can reinterpret the stories presented in their earlier work, and gain new perspectives on their worlds and existence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral Interest : Autobiography, Biography and Memoir. 4aPsychology : Death and Dying. 4aPsychology : Psychoanalysis. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842740940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438427409423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438427409/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles